item.title: Teleports [317] -- HELP PLOX :[
item.dc:creator: @adamhelloman8 adamhelloman8
item.description:
@adamhelloman8 wrote:

You have to find the button id. when you click one of the text’s, it should appear in your cmd prompt.

If it doesn’t, search for this in your client class

println("ab=

on the line above it, add you’re ingame name in the brackets, so its like this.

if(playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("youringamename")){ println("ab=" + actionButtonId); }

Than, when you click the option, in your cmd prompt it will say ab= ####

The #'s will be numbers.

When you got the id, search for that case in your clickingmost class.

Than make it teleport you to a location, by adding this.

c.triggerTele(2755, 2784, 0);

That’s just an example, change the 2755, 2784 to you’re coords.
